      • hasTransparency

        public boolean hasTransparency()
        Description copied from interface: View
        Indicates if the held animation has any transparency. If the held animation is opaque and covers the entire LED strip, then this should return false.

        If the held animation is opaque and covers the entire LED strip, then any effort spent rendering animations covered by this animation is wasted. Thus, this method serves as an optimization by indicating whether AnimationCompositor should render animations underneath this animation.

        Specified by:
        hasTransparency in interface View
        Returns:
        If the held animation has any transparency.
